The paper deals with vehicle re-identification using computer vision techniques, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves attention learning, which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also uses large-scale benchmark datasets, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM) research. Finally, the paper deals with security and privacy concerns related to vehicle identification, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
